    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1782-11-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1782-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="9" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d9">
                <head>*No. 4.<seg type="margin">[8]</seg>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#center">
                        <hi rend="italic">Articles between the
                                    United States of America and His Britannic Majesty</hi>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1782-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 30, 1782</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Article</hi> II.</p>
                <p>“From the northwest angle of Nova Scotia” * * * “through Lake Superior” *
                            * * “to the Long Lake; thence through the middle of said Long Lake, and
                            the water-communication between it and the Lake of the Woods, to the
                            said Lake of the Woods; thence through the said lake to the most
                            northwestern point thereof, and from thence on a due west course.” * * *
                            * *<seg type="margin">First treaty between the United States and Great
                                Britain adopts for boundary a due west course.</seg>
                </p>
            </div>
